Sometimes I just randomly think about how good @mura_masa_'s 'Someday Somewhere' EP was and still is.

A groundbreaking, absolute classic body of work from 2015, that will go down as the pinnacle of electronic production excellence from the @SoundCloud 2010's era.

So, if you see a small music blog putting in the work, be sure to appreciate them.

There's not many left, and if we want to see more editorial opportunities for new artists, these smaller blogs are so important for that.

Running a music blog gets incredibly fatiguing not because people don't really care at scale, but its when the artists don't appreciate the work.

A blue check + follower count does not make a music blog worth more, it's the time it's been around and the quality of its curation.
